item.title: Photography Collection #02 - Moment In Peking (The Autumn)
item.description: Preface It has been over a year since I came to Beijing. Due to long periods of staying in my small room and lacking the mood to explore, its four seasons have merely been the changing greenery on my way to work. I haven’t even visited the most well-known landmarks. In fact, I’ve moved between quite a few cities over the years. Each time, I always thought, “There’s still time,” “There are plenty of days ahead,” “There will always be a chance,” yet often left with many regrets.
